==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harmotome
<hw>Har"mo*tome</hw> <pr>(-m⟦osl⟧*t⟦omac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>"armo`s</grk> a joint + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut: cf.
F. <ets>harmotome</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A hydrous
silicate of alumina and baryta, occurring usually in white cruciform
crystals; cross-stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A related mineral, called <xex>lime harmotome</xex>, and
<xex>Phillipsite</xex>, contains lime in place of baryta.</note>
<rj><au>Dana.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harness</ent>⟦br⟧
